                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/26450: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Aden (<persName type="from"
                            >Timberlake</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Aden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-10T00:00:00+03:00"
                            >December 10, 1942—midnight.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 13—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. Have seen telegraph from London Foreign Office which states Platt’s
                    instructions are to throw French Somaliland to de Gaulle “using all means short
                    of serious bloodshed”. Please note use word serious.</p>
                <p>I feel very strongly the apparent British willingness to sacrifice not only the
                    fate of French Somaliland but also the present strong desire of its people to
                    cooperate in the Allied war effort to the satisfaction of a purely political
                    deal or promise to de Gaulle.</p>
                <p>Please await end my telegram No. 48 before instructing me further. A few days
                    will make no difference here.</p>
                <p>Date this telegram December 13, 6 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Timberlake</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
